  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ankle rehabilitation training becomes a tough question for the patients with ankle joint
      injuries especially with the hemiplegia after stroke. Here a novel powered ankle foot
      orthoses which can provide ankle dorsiflexion and plantar flexion assistant using electric
      motor is proposed in this paper. The mechanical structure of the orthoses includes wearing
      parts, ankle joint hinged part, driving unit, transmission mechanism and sensing units. This
      study provides a new method for ankle foot orthoses design and has great significance for
      ankle rehabilitation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
